criteria.driver_alignment:
DISCOVER — defined the objective to compute WACC for a specific investment decision;  
IMPLEMENT — used code/API to compute WACC and run a debt-issuance sensitivity scenario;  
REFLECT — discussed components/implications (CAPM for equity, tax deductibility of interest, high equity beta) demonstrating conceptual understanding.

DISCOVER — set objective to compute WACC (context for needing cost of equity);  
IMPLEMENT — used code/API to compute inputs and run scenarios (implementation of CAPM-derived value);  
REFLECT — discussed equity beta and implications for cost of equity, showing conceptual reflection.

DISCOVER — framed objective to evaluate additional debt financing impact on WACC;  
IMPLEMENT — used code/API to compute WACC and report the after-tax cost of debt;  
REFLECT — explicitly discussed tax deductibility/tax-shield effect and its influence on WACC.

DISCOVER — defined evaluating additional debt financing impact on WACC (context for tax shield);  
IMPLEMENT — used code/API to calculate WACC and after-tax cost of debt in scenarios;  
REFLECT — explicitly noted tax-deductibility of interest and its effect on lowering WACC.

DISCOVER — framed the assignment as using WACC to evaluate a $5B content investment;  
IMPLEMENT — built code and a sensitivity table to compute WACC under alternative capital structures;  
REFLECT — interpreted the computed WACC as a hurdle rate and discussed project-specific vs firmwide discounting.

Represent — student stated the goal and asked for code to compute WACC;  
Implement — student reports an API/code was used to run scenarios;  
Validate — student reports output values (WACC = 11.22, cost of equity 11.65%, after-tax debt 4.58%) but does not show verification steps.

Represent — student requested CAPM use and framed the task to compute cost of equity;  
Implement — student reports code/API was used to run calculations;  
Validate — student reports a final cost-of-equity value but provides no verification details.

Represent — student requested a coded approach and described using market values for total firm value;  
Implement — student reports using an API/code to run the calculation;  
Validate — student reports output WACC but provides no explicit verification or breakdown of market-value weight calculations.

Represent — requested a sensitivity analysis comparing baseline and $3B-debt scenarios;  
Implement — reports using code/API to generate the sensitivity table and scenario B;  
Validate — interprets and reports the resulting WACC differences from the sensitivity output.

DISCOVER — defined objective and requested an automated Python model to compute WACC;  
IMPLEMENT — reports using an API/code to run the calculation and produce scenarios;  
EVOLVE — produced a sensitivity table and discussed applying results to project decisions.

