DISCOVER — framed the problem and need for these components in the Netflix financing decision;  
IMPLEMENT/VALIDATE — requested code to operationalize the mapping and reports component values used.

DISCOVER — defined the WACC calculation objective and decision context;  
REPRESENT — specified an implementable model (Python) and the scenario structure;  
IMPLEMENT — executed the model/API to produce a sensitivity table comparing baseline and $3B-debt scenarios;  
VALIDATE/REFLECT — reported results (WACC values) and interpreted their implications.

DISCOVER — defined the WACC objective and decision context;  
IMPLEMENT — used code/API to compute WACC and scenarios;  
VALIDATE — reported internal results but provided no external sources or peer/industry comparisons.

DISCOVER — defined the capital-budgeting decision (hypothetical $5B content investment);  
IMPLEMENT — executed WACC calculation and scenarios to generate actionable outputs;  
EVOLVE/REFLECT — explicitly applied WACC as a hurdle rate and discussed project-specific vs firmwide discounting and audience-driven valuation implications.

DISCOVER — defined the decision context and intent to analyze capital-structure changes;  
IMPLEMENT — ran a scenario (issuance of $3B debt) and produced WACC results;  
